               <p>ANDREW WAKE. I am a <rs id="t18180114-103-viclabel543" type="occupation">brush-maker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180114-103-victim789 t18180114-103-viclabel543"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18180114-103-crimeloc544">Uxbridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180114-103-crimeloc544" type="placeName" value="Uxbridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180114-103-crimeloc544" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180114-103-off541 t18180114-103-crimeloc544"></join>. I <rs id="t18180114-103-viclabel545" type="occupation">sell shoes</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180114-103-victim789 t18180114-103-viclabel545"></join>. On the 13th of December I lost a pair of shoes from my shop, and followed the prisoner. When he saw me he began to run, and threw the shoes away. He had a stick with a three-pronged fork at the end. I secured him, and picked the shoes up.</p>
               <p>REBECCA WAKE. I and my brother were sitting by the fire. On looking into the shop, I saw the prisoner draw his arm from the counter and go out. We ran out - I saw him throw the shoes away.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I cannot deny it.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 46.</p>
               <p>Of <rs id="t18180114-103-verdict546" type="verdictDescription">
